|Parker}} ||'for his lifetime contribution to the foundations and development of [[Behavioral ecology|behavioural ecology]], in particular for understanding evolutionary adaptations and their consequences for natural populations.' |- |2010 || {{sortname|Bryan|Clarke}} || 'for his original and influential contributions to our understanding of the genetic basis of evolution.' |- |2012 || {{sortname|Tim|Clutton-Brock}} || 'for his outstanding work on the diversity of animal societies and demonstration of their effects on the evolution of [[Reproduction#Reproductive_strategies|reproductive strategies]], the operation of selection and the [[Population dynamics|dynamics of populations]].' |- |2014 || [[John Sutherland (chemist)|John Sutherland]] || 'for his novel and convincing work on [[Abiogenesis|prebiotic chemistry]], in particular his solution to the central problem of nucleoside synthesis.' |- |2016 || [[Caroline Dean]] || 'for her work addressing fundamental questions in the perception of temperature cues and how modifications in [[Epigenetics of plant growth and development|epigenetic mechanisms]] play an important role in adaptation.' |- |2018 || [[Bill Hill (geneticist)|William Hill]] || 'for his contribution to our understanding of the genetics of quantitative traits and response to selection' |- |}
